 United States Africa Command  US forces, in an advise-and-assist capacity, partnered with Somali forces in a raid targeting Islamic Al-Qaeda militants aligned with the Shabaab group on May 9. Ali Mohamed Moalin, a traditional elder who lives close to Afgoye in Lower Shabelle where the raid took place, said five “innocent farmers” were killed. AFRICOM said it had conducted a thorough review of the case. We “determined the allegations of civilian casualties to be not credible,” officials said in a statement. “As with any allegation of civilian casualties, US Africa Command reviewed all available relevant information concerning the incident.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .